------------------------------------------------------------
A. SID LAYER — STRUCTURAL PRIMITIVES
------------------------------------------------------------

SID.1  Typed Space
   G_[unit] : admissible carrier set
   ★ : G_[unit] × G_[unit] → G_[unit]
       (binary operator typed over G_[unit])

SID.2  Closure Condition
   For all a, b ∈ G_[unit]:
       a ★ b ∈ G_[unit]

SID.3  Associativity Condition
   For all a, b, c ∈ G_[unit]:
       (a ★ b) ★ c = a ★ (b ★ c)

SID.4  Identity Element
   ∃ e ∈ G_[unit] such that:
       e ★ a = a ★ e = a

SID.5  Inverse Element
   ∀ a ∈ G_[unit], ∃ a⁻¹ ∈ G_[unit] such that:
       a ★ a⁻¹ = a⁻¹ ★ a = e

SID.6  Abelian Condition (optional)
   ∀ a, b ∈ G_[unit]:
       a ★ b = b ★ a

------------------------------------------------------------
B. PED LAYER — OPERATIONAL ENGINE
------------------------------------------------------------

PED.1  Operation Engine
   Power(M,F) → evaluation of ★ over G_[unit]
   Evaluation(p,P) → morphism-level consistency
   Dynamics(Q_slice) → invertibility + identity stability

PED.2  Homomorphisms
   φ : G → H
   PED condition:
       φ(a ★ b) = φ(a) ★ φ(b)
   Kernel:
       Ker(φ) = { x ∈ G : φ(x) = e_H }
   Quotient:
       G / Ker(φ)  (PED-stable factorization)

PED.3  Group Actions
   α : G × X → X
   PED-flow:
       α(g₁ ★ g₂, x) = α(g₁, α(g₂, x))
   Stabilizer:
       Stab(x) = { g ∈ G : α(g, x) = x }
   Orbit:
       Orb(x) = { α(g, x) : g ∈ G }

PED.4  Representations
   ρ : G → GL(V)
   PED-linearization:
       ρ(a ★ b) = ρ(a) · ρ(b)
   Character:
       χ(g) = trace(ρ(g))

PED.5  Classification Engine
   Simple groups = PED-irreducible units:
       - Cyclic of prime order
       - Alternating Aₙ (n ≥ 5)
       - Lie-type families
       - 26 sporadic groups

